From: Dominik Brodowski <linux@dominikbrodowski.net>
Date: Sun, 11 Feb 2018 11:49:45 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] x86/entry/64: Introduce the PUSH_AND_CLEAN_REGS macro
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.15.5
Git-commit: 3f01daecd545e818098d84fd1ad43e19a508d705

commit 3f01daecd545e818098d84fd1ad43e19a508d705 upstream.

Those instances where ALLOC_PT_GPREGS_ON_STACK is called just before
SAVE_AND_CLEAR_REGS can trivially be replaced by PUSH_AND_CLEAN_REGS.
This macro uses PUSH instead of MOV and should therefore be faster, at
least on newer CPUs.

